1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:06,100
It sounds crazy, but I was the exact kind of person trapped in the self-help loop without even knowing it.

2
00:00:06,050 --> 00:00:08,162
I thought I was growing.

3
00:00:08,162 --> 00:00:11,562
But in reality, I was just consuming advice.

4
00:00:11,562 --> 00:00:15,400
Every day I picked up a new tip from some internet guru.

5
00:00:15,400 --> 00:00:17,025
A new book.

6
00:00:17,025 --> 00:00:18,912
A new routine.

7
00:00:18,912 --> 00:00:20,762
A new system.

8
00:00:20,762 --> 00:00:22,512
A new skill.

9
00:00:22,512 --> 00:00:25,887
A new "learn this and your life will change" promise.

10
00:00:25,887 --> 00:00:27,737
And the result?

11
00:00:27,737 --> 00:00:35,050
I wasted over a year strictly following useless advice... to the point where I didn't even know what actually worked for me anymore.

12
00:00:35,050 --> 00:00:37,387
I wasn't moving forward.

13
00:00:37,387 --> 00:00:39,825
I was just more confused.

14
00:00:39,825 --> 00:00:41,687
More exhausted.

15
00:00:41,687 --> 00:00:46,087
And the worst part is, I started thinking: "Is there something wrong with me?

16
00:00:46,087 --> 00:00:48,250
Do I lack discipline?

17
00:00:48,250 --> 00:00:50,962
Am I just not good enough to change?

18
00:00:50,962 --> 00:00:52,425
No.

19
00:00:52,425 --> 00:00:54,500
The problem isn't you.

20
00:00:54,500 --> 00:01:00,000
The problem is you are learning from a pile of advice that was never designed for your actual life.

21
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:05,425
You are using the fake busyness of "learning how to live" to escape the friction of actually living.

